   U.S. Geological Survey
   Center for Integration of Natural Disaster Information

   Drought

   The Drought Monitor site provides a detailed summary of US drought
   conditions by region. Drought Monitor represents a consensus of federal
   and academic scientists, of which USGS is a partner.
                             Recommended sites:
   USGS Drought Watch
   provides daily streamflow conditions based on real-time data
   collection.
   Drought links
   provided by Drought Monitor
   US Seasonal Drought Outlook
   prepared by the Climate Prediction Center, NCEP/NWS/NOAA
   National Drought Mitigation Center (NDMC)
   based at the University of Nebraska-Lincoln
   NDMC Directory
   of drought-related contacts listed by state and by organization/agency
   Drought Impacts in the US
   outlines drought recovery area and details state-by-state drought
   impacts
   NOAA's Drought Information Center
   USGS
   Drought Fact Sheet

